"The present study was designed to investigate the effect of sex on the pharmacokinetics of olanzapine in healthy volunteers. Thirty-six subjects (18 males and 18 females) were enrolled in this randomized, open-label, two-period, two-sequence crossover study. Olanzapine 10 mg was administered orally on two separate occasions with a 7-day washout period between the two dosing periods. Blood samples were collected for pharmacokinetic analysis at various time points up to 72 hours post-dose.

The area under the curve (AUC) and maximum concentration (Cmax) of olanzapine were determined by non-compartmental analysis. The AUC and Cmax values were not significantly different between males and females (p-value by Fisher's exact test: 0.31 for AUC and 0.51 for Cmax).

